                    <br>
                    <h3 style="position :relative;left:26%;border-style:none;">Full-Coverage Application Security Scanner :XTREME</h3>
					<br>
					<br>
					<div id="requirements">
					<div>
                                 <span class="btn btn-primary" style="cursor:default"><strong><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-play-circle"></span>  Requirements : (Xml Injection-Based Scans) - Phase 1 </strong></span>
                    </div>
				<br>
					<ul>
					<li>
					<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:150%;color:#444444;font-size:14px;"><strong>Technology support : </strong>Tool provides support for web applications developed using following languages : Python, PHP, Visual Basic, Java, C#, Ruby, Perl.</p>
					</li>
					<li>
					<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:150%;color:#444444;font-size:14px;"><strong>Back end Support : </strong>The tool provides support for any of the above mentioned technologies using Basex XML Database engine  at back end.Thus basex server needs to be installed on client machine that has web application to be tested.</p>
					</li>
					<li>
					<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:150%;color:#444444;font-size:14px;"><strong>Additional Requirements : </strong> The tool further requires Redis server ( key-value cache and store),to be installed and running on the client machine that has the web application to be tested.</p>
					</li>
					
					
					</div>
					<br>
					<br>
					<div id ="prerequisites " style="width:100%;background-color:white;">
					<div>
                                <span class="btn btn-primary" style="cursor:default"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-play-circle"></span> Prerequisites for usage</span>
                    </div>
					<br>
					<div style="">
					 <h4><strong>BasexClient File replacement Steps :</strong></h4>
					<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:150%;color:#444444;font-size:14px;">
					The tool follows a black box approach towards  detection of vulnerabilities in web applications and thus 
					driver modification for each technology is required to be done for capturing the queries that are sent to the database server. 
					BaseX client files were modified for the following web technologies with respect to BaseX server being used as the XML back end persistent store: 
					</p>
					<ul>
					<li>Python</li>
					<li>PHP</li>
					<li>Visual Basic</li>
           			<li>Java</li>
     				<li>C#</li>
					<li>Ruby</li>
					<li>Perl</li>
                    </ul>					
                   
					<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:150%;color:#444444;font-size:14px;">
					Any web application using any the above mentioned technologies and Basex server at the backed could be used to test for vulnerabilities using this tool.
					However a slight replacement needs to be done:<br>
					The basexClient  file of application under test needs to be replaced by the basexClient file provided here :
					<br>
					Following are the links to the modified driver files which could be downloaded and saved and then replaced with basexClient file of application to be tested.
					<ul>
					<li>Python &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="#">:&nbsp;&nbsp;BasexClient.py</a></li>
					<li>PHP &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="#">:&nbsp;&nbsp;BasexClient.php</a></li>
					<li>Visual Basic &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="#">:&nbsp;&nbsp;BasexClient.vb</a></li>
           			<li>Java &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="#">:&nbsp;&nbsp;BasexClient.java</a></li>
     				<li>C# &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="#">:&nbsp;&nbsp;BasexClient.c#</a></li>
					<li>Ruby &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="#">:&nbsp;&nbsp;BasexClient.rb</a></li>
					<li>Perl &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="#">:&nbsp;&nbsp;BasexClient.pl</a></li>
					</ul>
					</p>
					</div>
					<div>
				
					 <h4><strong>Basex installation :</strong></h4>
					 <ul>
					 <li>
					<a href="http://basex.org/products/download/all-downloads/" target="_blank">www.basex.org</a>
					 </li>
					 </ul>
					</div>
					<div>
					
					 <h4><strong>Redis Queue installation :</strong></h4>
					 <ul>
					 <li>
					<a href="http://redis.io/" target="_blank">www.redis.io</a>
					 </li>
					 </ul>
